arts.ttl: World Cup qualifying roundup: Germany crush Slovakia to seal spot as Dutch progress
arts.sum: Woltemade on target as Germany cruise to 6-0 victory Netherlands secure place with 4-0 win against Lithuania Germany secured a place at next year’s World Cup by crushing Slovakia 6-0 in their final qualifier, pummelling them into submission with four goals in the first half and sending their opponents into a playoff in March. The four-time world champions, who went out in the first round of the last two editions of the World Cup, finished top of their group, three points clear of Slovakia. Continue reading...
